spec: as3271
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(asyncio)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 665 (as3271): __rand__, __ror__, __rxor__ dict-presence (reflected bitwise logical) for asyncio types."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
    - "Classes covered: asyncio.Task, asyncio.Future, asyncio.Event, asyncio.Lock, asyncio.Semaphore, asyncio.BoundedSemaphore, asyncio.Condition, asyncio.Queue, asyncio.PriorityQueue, asyncio.LifoQueue."
    - "Key finding (__rand__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __rand__. Reflected bitwise AND (__rand__) is invoked when the left operand's __and__ returns NotImplemented — e.g., n & obj triggers obj.__rand__(n). asyncio types define no __and__ (confirmed false in wave 661), so __rand__ is equally absent. asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition are boolean-state synchronization guards; bitwise AND has no meaning for synchronization state objects. asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore manage an integer permit counter fully encapsulated behind acquire()/release() coroutines; the counter is not exposed for bitwise operations. asyncio.Task/Future are pending coroutine result handles; reflected bitwise AND is undefined for them. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue are ordered item stores with no bitwise data model."
    - "Key finding (__ror__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __ror__. Reflected bitwise OR (__ror__) is invoked when the left operand's __or__ returns NotImplemented. asyncio types define no __or__ (confirmed false in wave 661), so __ror__ is equally absent. Note: dict defines __or__ (merge operator, PEP 584, Python 3.9+) and __ror__, but asyncio types are not dict subclasses and implement no dict-merge protocol. asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition/Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: synchronization primitives with no bitwise semantics. asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles; __ror__ is absent. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores; reflected OR is entirely absent."
    - "Key finding (__rxor__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __rxor__. Reflected bitwise XOR (__rxor__) is invoked when the left operand's __xor__ returns NotImplemented. asyncio types define no __xor__ (confirmed false in wave 661), so __rxor__ is equally absent. asyncio types are coroutine-based concurrency primitives — their entire API surface is expressed through await, async with, async for, and explicit method calls. Neither forward nor reflected bitwise logical operators appear anywhere in the asyncio type hierarchy."
    - "Continues the unbroken all-false run from wave 656 (__call__/__len__/__getitem__) through wave 665 (__rand__/__ror__/__rxor__) — ten consecutive waves of 100% false results for asyncio types."
    - "Cross-wave summary for asyncio subjects:"
    - "  Wave 652 (as3076): __get__ — Task/Future/Queue/Handle true; others false."
    - "  Wave 653 (as3091): __hash__/__eq__/__bool__ — selected true."
    - "  Wave 654 (as3106): __lt__/__le__/__gt__ — TimerHandle true; others false."
    - "  Wave 655 (as3121): __ge__ — TimerHandle true; __repr__ — 12 classes true."
    - "  Wave 656 (as3136): __call__/__len__/__getitem__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 657 (as3151): __setitem__/__delitem__/__contains__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 658 (as3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 659 (as3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 660 (as3196): __pow__/__lshift__/__rshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 661 (as3211): __and__/__or__/__xor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 662 (as3226): __radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 663 (as3241): __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 664 (as3256): __rpow__/__rlshift__/__rrshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 665 (as3271): __rand__/__ror__/__rxor__ — all false for all 10."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __rand__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__rand__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __rand__.
# Reflected bitwise AND (__rand__) is invoked when the left operand's
#   __and__ returns NotImplemented — e.g., n & obj triggers obj.__rand__(n).
# asyncio types define no __and__ (confirmed false in wave 661), so
#   __rand__ is equally absent.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition: boolean-state synchronization guards;
#   n & event is not a defined Python expression.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: permit-counter objects; the counter
#   is fully encapsulated behind acquire()/release() coroutines.
# asyncio.Task/Future: pending coroutine result handles; reflected bitwise
#   AND is undefined for coroutine handles.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: ordered item stores with no
#   bitwise or logical data model of any kind.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

