# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __rxor__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__rxor__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __rxor__.
# Reflected bitwise XOR (__rxor__) is invoked when the left operand's
#   __xor__ returns NotImplemented — e.g., n ^ obj triggers obj.__rxor__(n).
# asyncio types define no __xor__ (confirmed false in wave 661), so
#   __rxor__ is equally absent.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition/Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: synchronization
#   primitives with no bitwise semantics of any kind.
# asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles; reflected bitwise XOR is
#   undefined for coroutine handles.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: queue types do not define
#   __xor__ or __rxor__; they manage items solely through put()/get()
#   coroutine calls.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

